# {{context|transitive|lang=en}} To bear [[patiently]]; to [[tolerate]]; to put up with; stand. {{defdate|First attested in the late 15<sup>th</sup> century.}}<ref name=SOED/>
#* {{RQ:Shakespeare Henry 4-2|III-ii}}
#*: She could not '''abide''' Master Shallow.
